\begin_layout Chapter
Direction Selectivity in the Off SAC
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The starburst amacrine cell is a critical player in the direction selectivity
 circuit.
 A SAC dendrite is more activated by motion outward from the cell body to
 the tip of the dendrite, than by motion in the opposite direction 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Euler:2002oq"

\end_inset

.
 Therefore a SAC dendrite exhibits DS, and outward motion is said to be
 its 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

preferred direction.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 Note that it is incorrect to assign a single such direction to a SAC, because
 each of the cell's dendrites has its own preferred direction (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Off-BC-renderings"

\end_inset

a).
 DS persists after blocking inhibitory synaptic transmission 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Hausselt:2007nx"

\end_inset

, when the only remaining inputs to SACs are bipolar cells (BCs), which
 are excitatory.
 Since the SAC exhibits DS, while its BC inputs do not 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Yonehara:2013hc"

\end_inset

, we say that DS 
\emph on
emerges
\emph default
 from the BC-SAC circuit.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mouse BCs have been classified into multiple types 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "wassle2009cone"

\end_inset

, with different time lags in visual response 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Baden:2013uq,Borghuis:2013uq"

\end_inset

.
 Motion is a spatiotemporal phenomenon: an object at one location appears
 somewhere else after a time delay.
 Therefore we wondered whether DS might arise because different locations
 on the SAC dendrite are wired to BC types with different time lags.
 More specifically, we hypothesized that the proximal BCs (wired near the
 SAC soma) lag the distal BCs (wired far from the soma).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

space-time wiring specificity
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 could lead to DS as follows (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Hypothesized-Models-of"

\end_inset

c).
 Motion outward from the soma will activate the proximal BCs followed by
 the distal BCs.
 If the stimulus speed is appropriate for the time lag, signals from both
 BC groups will reach the SAC dendrite simultaneously, summing to produce
 a large depolarization.
 For motion inward towards the soma, BC signals will reach the SAC dendrite
 asynchronously, causing only small depolarizations.
 Therefore the dendrite will 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

prefer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 outward motion, as observed experimentally 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Euler:2002oq"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Contact analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We reconstructed 195 Off BC axons and 79 Off SACs from e2198 (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Reconstructed-off"

\end_inset

b).
 The e2198 retina was stained in an unconventional way that did not mark
 intracellular structures such as neurotransmitter vesicles 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Briggman:2011zr"

\end_inset

, and reliable morphological criteria for identification of BC presynaptic
 terminals are unknown.
 As an indirect measure of connectivity, contact areas were computed for
 all BC-SAC pairs.
 The resulting 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

contact matrix
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 was analyzed through two subsequent steps.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the first step, Off BC axons were classified into five cell types, following
 structural criteria 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Helmstaedter:2013zr"

\end_inset

 established to correspond with previous molecular definitions 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "wassle2009cone"

\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-bc-splitting"

\end_inset

).
 BC types stratify at characteristic depths in the inner plexiform layer
 (IPL), and vary in size (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset

a).
 The BCs of each type formed a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

mosaic,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 meaning that cells were spaced roughly periodically (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Off-BC-renderings"

\end_inset

a-e).
 This is generally accepted as an important defining property of a retinal
 cell type.
 Type densities (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Off-BC-renderings"

\end_inset

f) were roughly consistent with previous reports 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "wassle2009cone"

\end_inset

.
 When the columns of the contact matrix were sorted by BC type (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset

b), it became evident that BC2 and BC3a contact SACs more than other BC
 types.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the second step, we averaged contact area over BC-SAC pairs of the same
 BC type and similar distance between the BC axon and the SAC soma in the
 plane tangential to the retina (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset

c).
 These absolute areas were normalized to convert them into the percentage
 of SAC surface area covered by BCs of a given type (Methods).
 The resulting graphs show that BC2 prefers to contact SAC dendrites close
 to the SAC soma, whereas BC3a prefers to contact far from the soma (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset

d, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Alternative-contact-OFF"

\end_inset

c).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
---
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Edges of the affinity graph connecting BC with SAC voxels were defined as
 BC-SAC contact edges.
 For each pair, the sum of the edges yielded an estimate of contact area.
 The Euclidean distance separating each BC-SAC pair was computed after projectin
g their centers onto the SAC plane.
 Centers of SAC somata were manually annotated, and centers of BC arbors
 were computed as the centroids of their surface voxels.
 The pairs were binned by distance of the BC from the SAC soma.
 For every pair in a bin, the fraction of SAC surface area devoted to BC-SAC
 contact within the convex hull of the BC was computed as the ratio of BC-SAC
 contact edges to SAC surface edges within the convex hull.
 The latter was estimated by the number of SAC surface voxels multiplied
 by a geometric conversion factor of 1.4 SAC surface edges per surface voxel.
 (This factor was estimated by dividing the total number of SAC surface
 edges by the total number of SAC surface voxels in the volume.) BC-SAC pairs
 with fewer than 10,000 SAC surface voxels inside the hull were excluded
 from the computation to reduce the effect of fluctuations.
 The ratios for BCs of the same type were averaged for each distance bin
 and multiplied by a mosaic overlap factor to yield the values in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset

d.
 The mosaic overlap factor represents the extent to which neighboring convex
 hulls overlap one another, which varies by cell type.
 This factor was computed by dividing the sum of the hull areas for each
 cell by the area of the union of hulls for each cell type.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In instances where edges in the affinity graph are converted to area in
 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{}m^{2}$
\end_inset

, the conversion factor of 291.5
\begin_inset Formula $\text{}m^{2}$
\end_inset

 per edge is used.
 This factor estimates the real surface area of the cell given the different
 possible orientations of edges and effects from pixelization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename off_sac papers/figure4.eps

\end_inset


\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
BC-Off SAC contact.

\series bold
 
\series default

\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:off-SAC-contact"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Box Frameless
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
