\series default
, The same SACs appear similar when viewed along the light axis.
 A BC axon (green) is much smaller.
 Black circles and gray dots respectively indicate reconstructed On and
 Off SAC cell body locations.
 On BCs were reconstructed in a patch (dashed rectangle).
 Scale bar, 
\begin_inset Formula $50~\mu$
\end_inset

m,
\end_layout

