\begin_layout Section
BC-SAC co-stratification analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:alignment"

\end_inset

d already showed that proximal SAC dendrites span a wide range of IPL depths,
 which are different from the depths of the intermediate and distal dendrites.
 Because of this depth difference, the proximal zone co-stratifies with
 BC7 but only weakly with BC5, which is consistent with our observed preference
 of BC7 for contact with the proximal zone.
 Such reasoning was already used by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Famiglietti:1991fk"

\end_inset

 to infer that proximal dendrites should receive inputs from different BC
 types compared to distal dendrites.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This suggests that co-stratification could be used to quantitatively predict
 On BC-SAC contact using the integral over depth of the product of BC and
 SAC stratification profiles.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Wiring-specificity-ON"

\end_inset

d shows that this prediction works well in some respects, but not in others.
 On the one hand, predicted contact (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Wiring-specificity-ON"

\end_inset

d) nicely matches actual contact (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Wiring-specificity-ON"

\end_inset

c) for BC5t, BC5i, and BC7, failing only to match the observed decrease
 in the distal zone.
 On the other hand, actual contact of BC6 is much lower than expected from
 predicted contact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may seem surprising that BC6 makes little contact with On SACs, given
 that it stratifies over a broad range of IPL depths that includes all zones
 of On SAC dendrites (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Classification-of-On"

\end_inset

a).
 One reason may be that the BC6 stratification profile dips down exactly
 at the depth of intermediate and distal dendrites (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Classification-of-On"

\end_inset

c), as if BC6 were trying to avoid contacting the On SAC.
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename figure5.eps

\end_inset


\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Wiring specificity of On BC-SAC circuit.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Wiring-specificity-ON"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Box Frameless
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
